    "body": "It probably makes sense to wait for https://github.com/status-im/status-react/pull/5330 https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4432 to be done since this issue requires communication with native API. For OSX this could be:\r\n```obj-c\r\n[[NSApp dockTile] setBadgeLabel:[NSString stringWithFormat:@\"%d\", newCount]];\r\n```\r\n\r\nMaybe it makes sense to add this code to snorenotify repo https://github.com/status-im/snorenotify/blob/master/src/plugins/backends/osxnotificationcenter/osxnotificationcenter.mm to avoid routine of creating new module just to make single API call.\r\n\r\n@MaxRis what do you think?\n\n<blockquote><img src=\"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/11767950?s=400&v=4\" width=\"48\" align=\"right\"><div><img src=\"https://assets-cdn.github.com/favicon.ico\" height=\"14\"> GitHub</div><div><strong><a href=\"https://github.com/status-im/snorenotify\">status-im/snorenotify</a></strong></div><div>Snorenotify is a multi platform Qt notification framework. Using a plugin system it is possible to create notifications with many different notification systems on Windows, Mac OS and Unix and mobi...</div></blockquote>",
